{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"AnimationEvent.initAnimationEvent()","mdn_url":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/AnimationEvent","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent\"><code>AnimationEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><em><code>AnimationEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/animationName\"><code>animationName</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/elapsedTime\"><code>elapsedTime</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/pseudoElement\"><code>pseudoElement</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"summary","title":"Summary","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <code><strong>AnimationEvent.initAnimationEvent()</strong></code> method Initializes an animation event created using the deprecated <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Document/createEvent\" title=\"Document.createEvent(\" animationevent\")\"=\"\"><code>Document.createEvent(\"AnimationEvent\")</code></a> method.</p>\n\n<p><code>AnimationEvent</code> created this way are untrusted.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect1\">\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> During the standardization process, this method was removed from the specification. It has been deprecated and is in the progress of being removed from most implementations. <strong>Do not use this method</strong>; instead, use the standard constructor, <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/AnimationEvent\" title=\"AnimationEvent()\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>AnimationEvent()</code></a>, to create a synthetic <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent\"><code>AnimationEvent</code></a>.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><em>animationEvent</em>.initAnimationEvent(<em>typeArg</em>, <em>canBubbleArg</em>, <em>cancelableArg</em>, <em>animationNameArg</em>, <em>elapsedTimeArg</em>);</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"typearg\"><code>typeArg</code></dt>\n <dd>A <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String_6fa58bba0570d663099f0ae7ae8883ab\"><code>DOMString</code></a> identifying the specific type of animation event that occurred. The following values are allowed:\n <table>\n  <thead>\n   <tr>\n    <th scope=\"col\">Value</th>\n    <th scope=\"col\">Meaning</th>\n   </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n   <tr>\n    <td><code>animationstart</code></td>\n    <td>The animation has started.</td>\n   </tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><code>animationend</code></td>\n    <td>The animation completed.</td>\n   </tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><code>animationiteration</code></td>\n    <td>The current iteration just completed.</td>\n   </tr>\n  </tbody>\n </table>\n </dd>\n <dt id=\"canbubblearg\"><code>canBubbleArg</code></dt>\n <dd>A <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> flag indicating if the event can bubble (<code>true</code>) or not (<code>false)</code>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"cancelablearg\"><code>cancelableArg</code></dt>\n <dd>A <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> flag indicating if the event associated action can be avoided (<code>true</code>) or not (<code>false)</code>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"animationnamearg\"><code>animationNameArg</code></dt>\n <dd>A <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String_6fa58bba0570d663099f0ae7ae8883ab\"><code>DOMString</code></a> containing the value of the <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-name\"><code>animation-name</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> CSS property associated with the transition.</dd>\n <dt id=\"elapsedtimearg\"><code>elapsedTimeArg</code></dt>\n <dd>A <code>float</code> indicating the amount of time the animation has been running, in seconds, as of the time the event was fired, excluding any time the animation was paused. For an <code>\"animationstart\"</code> event, <code>elapsedTime</code> is <code>0.0</code> unless there was a negative value for <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-delay\">animation-delay</a></code>, in which case the event will be fired with <code>elapsedTime</code> containing  <code>(-1 * </code><em>delay</em><code>)</code>.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-animations/#dom-animationevent-animationevent","title":"CSS Animations Level 2"}],"query":"api.AnimationEvent.AnimationEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.AnimationEvent.AnimationEvent","dataURL":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/AnimationEvent/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Animations/Using_CSS_animations\">Using CSS animations</a></li>\n <li>Animation-related CSS properties and at-rules: <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation\"><code>animation</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-delay\"><code>animation-delay</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-direction\"><code>animation-direction</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-duration\"><code>animation-duration</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/CSS/animation-fill-mode\"><code>animation-fill-mode</code></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-iteration-count\"><code>animation-iteration-count</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-name\"><code>animation-name</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-play-state\"><code>animation-play-state</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-timing-function\"><code>animation-timing-function</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>, <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@keyframes\"><code>@keyframes</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a>.</li>\n <li>The <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent\"><code>AnimationEvent</code></a> interface it belongs to.</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Summary","id":"summary"},{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The AnimationEvent.initAnimationEvent() method Initializes an animation event created using the deprecated Document.createEvent(\"AnimationEvent\") method.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"AnimationEvent()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"zh-tw/web/api/animationevent/animationevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/zh-tw/web/api/animationevent/animationevent/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/zh-TW/docs/Web","title":"給開發者的網頁技術文件"},{"uri":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent","title":"AnimationEvent"},{"uri":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/AnimationEvent/AnimationEvent","title":"AnimationEvent.initAnimationEvent()"}],"pageTitle":"AnimationEvent.initAnimationEvent() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}